title: Narrative

Vertical interactive `<<tabs>>` with `class:"tc-vertical"` compared to the static-tabs auto-delegated rendering. Static rendering ignores the vertical orientation since each tab becomes its own block-level card.

+
title: Output

;Interactive vertical tabs

<<tabs "[[SampleTabOne]] [[SampleTabTwo]] [[SampleTabThree]] [[SampleTabFour]]" "SampleTabOne" "$:/state/test/static-tabs/vertical" "tc-vertical">>

-----

;Static-render mode (tv-config-static="yes" auto-delegates; class="tc-vertical" passes through but has no effect on stacked cards)

<$let tv-config-static="yes">
<<tabs "[[SampleTabOne]] [[SampleTabTwo]] [[SampleTabThree]] [[SampleTabFour]]" "SampleTabOne" "$:/state/test/static-tabs/vertical-static" "tc-vertical">>
</$let>
